HEADWORD: Phototherapy
<hw>Pho`to*ther"a*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>The application of light for therapeutic purposes, esp. for
treating diseases of the skin.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Pho`to*the*rap"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<wf>Pho`to*ther`a*peu"tic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

